    "created_at": "2017-04-30T15:40:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-30T15:42:13Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This PR poses a conundrum given the discussion in https://github.com/forcecore/yupgi_alert0/pull/87 and now @GraionDilach's engine fork.\r\n\r\nOn the one hand I think its unreasonable for us to force community mods to fork everything that they want to modify, but on the other hand I don't like the idea of us making upstream changes for the sake of compatibility with code that has design issues that would prevent it from being merged upstream as-is.  This is a topic that we have not yet given serious thought to.\r\n\r\nFor this PR specifically, looking at https://github.com/forcecore/yupgi_alert0/pull/87 I would expect `AIDeployHelper` to call `ResolveOrder` instead of reaching directly into the internals of `DeployToUpgrade`, and `EnterSpawner` should be working with info passed into the virtual methods (which may require some changes to the method signatures).\r\n\r\nThe problem with making the internals of these classes less private is that it might (a) be reverted in the future as a code style cleanup by somebody who doesn't know it's being used downstream, or (b) prevent us from making necessary changes because we're worried about breaking downstream code.\r\n\r\nConsidering that the community seems to have already made up its mind about forking the engine, it might just be easier to direct these kind of compatibility fixes there... but that doesn't seem reasonable either."
  },
