    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": ">For this PR specifically, looking at forcecore/yupgi_alert0#87 I would expect AIDeployHelper to call ResolveOrder instead of reaching directly into the internals of DeployToUpgrade\r\n\r\nThis is something I've written a PR already for but seems it got lost during a refactor already (although true that my PR back then broke undeployable actors, something I overlooked back then and only fixed earlier today).\r\n\r\nActually, this ticket was among the main reasons why I forked, because this ticket + related ultimately would have forced Mods.AS into a dependency of yupgi_alert, preventing me on AS side to take code from it due to namespace conflicts thenafter. (To stop the misassumptions I've noticed in the IRC logs, the other ones were the already-mentioned actor variations possibility in https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/issues/12554#issuecomment-271105904, and my bad experiences in regards to #11624 and #11311. My personal development habits has nothing to do with my decision to softfork.)\r\n\r\nI actually consider this PR aggressive in terms even, because it tried to adjust three projects for one person's workflow."
